<p>When, in real life, something seems to happen without a cause, weâ€™re bothered by it. We go looking for a cause. Sometimes we go to extreme lengths, inventing myths or whole religions just to explain what makes the rain or who puts presents under the tree on Christmas morning. So feed the reader what the meal he wants! If something is happening, tell him who is doing what to whom!</p>

