<p>Play with words. Cultivate habits of crossword-puzzling, punning, rapping, rhyming and, as George Constanza says, â€œbebopping and scatting.â€ You may or may not be able to scat in whatever it is youâ€™re writing now, but wordplay will stretch your mind and make you more comfortable with writing and words in general. Let words be your sandbox.</p>

